INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("20","acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a","What is the gospel? Why does God allow suffering in the world? How could a loving God send people to hell? How can one religion claim to be \'the only way\'? The Inconvenient God will walk through these basic questions of belief and the overarching story that the Bible tells. If you have questions or are exploring Christianity, this class is a great place to start. \r\n\r\nWeek 1: Intro Week 2: Is the Bible God’s Word? Week 3: The problem with hell Week 4: If God is good why is there suffering? Week 5: What is the gospel? Week 6: Q & A");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("20","6055f16b-c2d8-4f28-bad2-9e121e3d1a82","\"I was on a slippery slope regarding my faith because I didn\'t fully understand why God allowed certain things to happen in my life so it was hard for me to trust Him.  Now that I know what God\'s purpose and mission is through us, it is so much easier for me to obediently follow without thinking why am I doing this.\"   \"I feel like before this class I was very dead inside.  I didn\'t have a heart for Jesus.  I didn\'t seek His influence in my life nor did I see it.  I had a lot of problems with scripture that were creating am emotional barrier in my relationship with Jesus.  More than anything I wanted to get over these problems but I couldn\'t do it on my own.  Taking this class helped me discover things about God that struck fear, awe, and love into my heart  So many of the things we learned I had known previously on an intellectual level, and although Ronnie was a great teacher, it was purely God\'s influence that let me believe it in my heart.  He answered my prayer, and I am tremendously grateful that he provided this class as a means to do so.\"   \"It shakes you up.  My foundation, my footing, is more uncertain.  And I think that is a good thing.  Not easy.  But good.\"");
