INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("52","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","The Lord saved me from a life of trying to save myself while I was in my teens. Since that day I have been learning what it means to be His child and to live on mission for His glory. I grew up in Canada and went to a small bible college where God continued to grab hold of me. During this season I read and was inspired by A.W. Tozer, George Muller, Jonathan Edwards, Charles Spurgeon, and John Piper. Through these men God showed me more clearly He is sovereign and I am not. After graduation I moved to the US where I attended Reformed Theological Seminary and have served as a pastor and director of a biblical counseling center.God has blessed me with an amazing wife and five incredible children, four of whom are adopted. Along with the privilege of pastoring at the Austin Stone I have the joy of serving with the ABBA Fund and Together for Adoption mobilizing God\'s people to live out the gospel for the sake of the orphan. My vision for the Stone is to become a place where God\'s people are both radically mobilized for God\'s mission and deeply cared for through gospel community.");
