INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("54","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","I was called to Christ when I was 13 years old, but I believe the process of sanctification really began to take effect while studying Romans as a leader in Bible Study Fellowship. This was my first introduction to Reformed theology, and the time when I really began to feel the Spirit working in my life. Since that time, I\'ve grown to love Scripture more with each day, and am constantly humbled by the application of the truths they contain. I was born in Fort Worth, TX, and have lived in Lubbock, TX and Memphis, TN. I moved to the Austin area in 2002 and worked as a Marketing leader in the High Tech Industry. My wife Shanna and I met while in college at Texas Tech University and were married in May of 1999. We have three children: Jackson, Will, and Brooklyn. In May of 2010, I completed my MBA at The Fuqua School of Business at Duke University. I\'ve served The Austin Stone in various leadership roles on the Audio/Visual/Lights/Camera (AVLC) team, pre-marital counseling, missional community, and the Financial Training ministry. My vision for the church is that we would be God\'s tool to radically grow people\'s love of Jesus in the city of Austin and globally and that we would breed generations upon generations of new believers with an excitement for living on mission.");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("55","919e8599-c2fe-46ae-b177-78dcef40d77b","Kim");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("55","278956b7-de5e-4111-af94-ae1c0daa398d","Tyler, Grayson, and Bentley");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("55","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","I was raised by parents who were great examples of faith in God. In college, God\'s plan for me became very tangible. His sovereignty and providence were clearly shown to me in those years.Our family has been going to The Austin Stone for almost 6 years now. My wife Kim and I have 2 boys (Tyler and Grayson) and a baby girl (Bentley). We\'ve served The Austin Stone as missional community leaders, small group leaders in the nearly/newly wed and the married life classes, as well as serving as marriage mentors. I\'ve been in professional sales/sales management for 10 years primarily selling technology products and services.  Most recently, I spent the last two years in business development and marketing leadership positions with companies building their businesses in Austin. I\'m a graduate of Baylor University with a B.B.A. in Marketing.  I enjoy any and all opportunities to network and get people together.  I wants to see the men and women of The Austin Stone develop into the leaders that bring God the most glory. I feel abundantly blessed that I have the opportunity to serve in a church that exists for the supremacy of the name and purpose of Jesus Christ.");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("56","919e8599-c2fe-46ae-b177-78dcef40d77b","Julie");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("56","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","I strive to love the Lord “with everything”… heart, soul, mind, and strength. Although my prideful heart is prone to wander, Christ continues to pursue me with an unfailing love. I\'m a husband to my beautiful wife, Julie, and father to two young sons, Noah and Hunter. We live in Cedar Park where we host a missional community.  After graduating from Texas A&M, I started a day-trading company and a granite countertop company (Summit Stoneworks).  I\'ve been actively serving at The Austin Stone since the Fulmore Middle School days, and most recently, have lead the church\'s finance team and helped oversee the collection of our tithes/offerings. I continually pray for humility- knowing that only through the power of the Holy Spirit and Christ in me can I glorify God in my marriage, my family, my workplace, and in our church.");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("57","919e8599-c2fe-46ae-b177-78dcef40d77b","Catherine");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("57","278956b7-de5e-4111-af94-ae1c0daa398d","Devin Ross, Logan, Meagan, and Graceyn");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("57","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","Jesus saved me from a self-centered, complacent, worldly existence of shallow faith, and saved me into a relationship that changed the center of my universe and changed the point of reference from which my motivation and identity is derived. My wife Catherine and I have been married 22 years. We have been blessed with four truly amazing kids – Devin Ross, Logan, Meagan, and Graceyn. I have been in practice as an Ob/Gyn in Austin for 17 years and am currently with Renaissance Women’s Group. The Austin Stone has been our church home since 2004. I am currently involved with our partnership in N. Africa and with small group coaching. The power to change hearts is God’s, and evidence of that is seen here at The Austin Stone over and over again, because we exist for the supremacy of the name and purpose of Jesus Christ!");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("58","919e8599-c2fe-46ae-b177-78dcef40d77b","Jenn");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("58","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","My wife Jenn and I have lived in Austin for 15 years and have been going to The Austin Stone for 6 years. We have two boys, Caleb and Luke, and reside in Round Rock. My wife and I currently serve in the premarital/newlywed and marriage ministries and before that were community group leaders. I graduated from The University of Texas at Austin with a BS in Architectural Engineering. My occupation of 12 years is as a Construction Manager/General Contractor. I balance my work hours with much rest in leisure with family and friends, especially when you add a little BBQ, music, or watching sports. Though my life did not follow a Sunday school example to a tee, I\'ve felt God’s presence and calling in my life as far back as I can remember.  Life for me has been a process filled with imperfections yet also with great teachers and the Word itself, and hopefully I\'ll continue to be matured and used for God’s good will. My desire is for God to be glorified in the highest all around me, and for Jesus the Christ to be the primary satisfying value in my life and all peoples’ lives.");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("59","919e8599-c2fe-46ae-b177-78dcef40d77b","Brooke");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("59","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","I fell in love with Jesus in college. One night after a Christian event in San Angelo, Texas, God came to me and introduced me to real faith. Before that I lived a life devoted to looking good for people by staying out of trouble and doing the right things. I thought that was what it meant to be a Christian, and it seemed to be the best way to get what I wanted in life. Since college, I have come to realize that following Christ in faith means trusting Him right now and for my future. My walk with Jesus has grown over the years as I have seen His faithfulness to his call over and over again. God put me together with my wife, Brooke, in 2001 while I was still in San Angelo. We lived in Dallas for a couple of years after that, before moving to Austin in 2004. We became partners with The Austin Stone shortly after in 2004. We now have two children, Luke and Carly Kate. Professionally, I recently stepped away from a  career as an actuary to follow a call to create a magazine designed to encourage the local church in Austin with stories of what God is doing around town. This has been quite an adventure in faith for a guy who graduated with a math degree! Sounds crazy sometimes, but so does building an ark, I guess. You hear the voice of Jesus, you believe him and you do what He says. You trust Him with everything and find out what He’s doing later.My involvement in ministry here at The Austin Stone has been in marriage counseling and missional community, along with helping to coordinate offering volunteers each month. My vision for the church is for our grandchildren to exist “for the supremacy of the name and purpose of Jesus Christ”, holding fast to the word of God and sound doctrine and teaching their children to carry on in it as well.");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("60","919e8599-c2fe-46ae-b177-78dcef40d77b","Karen");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("60","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","Jesus transformed my life 17 years ago, when my selfishness and need for approval were exposed in such a way that my only hope was the saving grace of Jesus Christ. It is only through the power of the Holy Spirit, that He continues to refine me and propel me to serve others in His Name. My wife Karen and I serve the body of The Austin Stone in leading the pre-marital mentoring ministry. Our passion is to share with couples that their marriage depends on the Gospel and our vision is to see their marriages display and proclaim Christ to others.We have three children and live in Central Austin. I graduated from The University of Texas and for work, own a recruiting firm, RG Search, that specializes in executive search.");
