INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("86","765421ed-4434-4a54-8bde-639b64311d77","JohnMurk");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("86","4b686386-9863-4505-9f5c-63b779a04e7e","I became a Christian relatively early in life, around 2nd or 3rd grade. I don’t remember exactly how old I was, but I do remember sitting on the front steps of my house, pondering things that I had been learning from my parents, my older sister, and my church. I knew that I had done some bad things in my life, things that God did not want me to do. But I also knew that He loved me and had sent Jesus to die in my place, and that if I believed these things, and that Jesus rose from the dead, that God would forgive me and I could live with Him forever. I prayed right there on the steps, just as I had learned in Vacation Bible School, and told God that I loved Him and wanted to follow Him. I know God’s timing is perfect, because it was shortly after this event that I encountered some large challenges in my life. Without a personal relationship with Jesus Christ, I cannot say for certain that I would have been able to make it through. That is why I am so passionate about ministering to children. I know first hand how important it is for children to have a close relationship with the one true, active, living God. I know that it is just as important for children to know Jesus Christ as Savior and to have the Holy Spirit as a guide as it is for an adult. It is my prayer that all children who come to Austin Stone will come to intimately know the One who created them, the One who saved them, and the One who loves them. I consider myself very blessed to be a part of what God is doing in the lives of the children at our church.");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("87","d7c483ed-b6d6-466d-b389-29dfbaa7f576","\"My vision for The Austin Stone is that as we continually pursue Jesus Christ and allow Him to direct our steps. My vision is that as people continue to meet Christ and experience Him at The Austin Stone, they are also empowered and equipped to be the “disciple-makers” in this world ensuring the Gospel reaches the “remotest parts of the earth.”");
INSERT INTO jos_zoo_search_index VALUES("87","1147fade-a7be-4b44-9ad8-9a13ed72719b","1 Timothy 4:12 – “Let no one look down on your youthfulness, but rather in speech, conduct, love, faith and purity, show yourself an example of those who believe.\" This speaks to the heart of any young person that the ministry of the Gospel and embodying Christ’s love is not reserved for a later season in life. The “fields are white for harvest.” The time is now.");
